                   <span class="css-chan6m">
                    Jul 17, 2023

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Amazing service....Chely is such a sweet lady and provides friendly and attentive service.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   This place was voted best Birrieria tacos for several years running so we of course ordered the queso Birrieria tacos...ordered the plate of 4 to share between 2 people and we each could only get thru one.  They were hearty and flavorful.  I found the consomm to have a strange flavor (clove?)  and chose not to use it.  We added a side of beans and rice, doused them in the delicious hot sauce on the table and were happy the portion was large enough for leftovers.  Our table also ordered the asada tacos which were one of the best we've ever had....when ordering, you'll be asked if you want homemade tortillas or packaged.  Do yourself a favor and get the homemade....obviously!  They are fantastic and you can see them coming hot off the griddle.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Pro tip: order some homemade tortillas to go...a little butter and salt makes a perfect late night snack.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Now for the cons:  The michelada looked beautiful and was refreshing.  The best part was it was served with jicama and cucumbers sprinkled with hot sauce and tajin on top.  There were also 4 shrimp, but they had not been cleaned and they still had the poop track :( Disappointing.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Lastly, The bathroom was really dirty and there was a large cockroach inside.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   If you can look past these few things, give it a try....it's worth it just for the tortillas.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   I came here from Bakersfield to buy my coworkers some breakfast burritos. I read solid reviews about this place, so I thought I'd give it a try.  While waiting on my breakfast burritos, Bertha gave me a cup of Birria. This was a very nice gesture. This is the first time trying goat Birria and I must say, this is the best Birria I've ever had. Very tasty and right blend of spices. And then, Fernando started talking to me and we shared stories about our cultures and how many similarities we have between the Hispanic and Asian cultures. I thoroughly enjoyed our conversation. I eventually got the breakfast burritos, they were huge and very good as well. I give this place five stars for food taste and quality. Five stars for customer service. And five stars for being so personable and having genuine conversations to build relationships with their customers. I can't wait to come back to Fresno just to eat here. Great job to this mom &amp; pop restaurant!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Quick service, and they were generous with the onion, cilantro, and salsa as requested. They gave us 3 lemon halves, but they were just chucked into the carry-out bag. I guess that's just how it goes sometimes lol.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I really enjoyed their adobada, however the asada was a little burnt. I'm a fan of handmade tortillas, but neither me nor my bf could eat a single of their tacos without the whole tortilla ripping through the center. Also ordered their quesobirria tacos, but they were extremely heavy with grease.
                  </span>

                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Hands down the best Birria in Fresno! Actually in Calwa. We came here for breakfast. They are open early 7 days a week. As the name suggests, they are known for their Birria which was voted the best at some point where they have proudly displayed a sign. My husband loves their menudo, he gets it with the pata. It's rich red color and stickiness tells you it's authentic. They could put it in a larger bowl but the small is sufficient to fill you up. The quest Birria is my favorite. You get four hardshell tacos dipped in Birria with cheese holding the meat together and a side of consomm. Every bite is heaven. Introduce yourself to you favorite Birria spot.
                  </span>

                   </a>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   This restaurant was introduced to us by a friend who ordered us some beef birria tacos with consom and they were absolutely delicious.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   When I was looking at their online menu, I saw that they had birria de chivo available and I was so surprised because it's becoming more and more rare to find birria de chivo! I hadn't had birria de chivo since I was in high school! My husband was very excited because this was a dish he missed a lot and hadn't had any since he was 10 years old! So of course we had to go try!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   It is an unassuming and humble restaurant. We were greeted by a friendly server. Upon entering the restaurant, I noticed the beautiful murals featuring famous Mexican mariachi singers - Pedro Infante, Jorge Negrete, Antonio Aguilar...the classics.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   And this place did not disappoint! We both got the birria de chivo plate which comes with rice, beans and handmade tortillas! Yes, handmade :) Large portions - both my husband and I had some delicious birria leftover.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   There are some bones in the birria, which the tender meat does fall off of (for those that are wary about bones); however there is an abundance of tender and juicy meat. Super flavorful and delicious birria!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I recommend this place, especially if you haven't had birria de chivo. Great service, great food, clean restaurant. Give their beef birria a try too!
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   !!    The birria tacos are bomb, their rice and beans are amazing.  !!!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Carne asada was ok, chewy and had bits that were a bit salt but the rice and beans inside made up for it
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Their green salsa was hella good AND spicy, the red one was good but not too spicy.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The service was great and I love how they have a sink in the open area to immediately wash your hands after some juicy birria.  Don't tell anyone, but this is right next to my suegras birria.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Los tacos de birria son una bomba, su arroz y frijoles son increbles. !!!
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   La carne asada estaba bien, masticable y tena trozos que estaban un poco salados, pero el arroz y los frijoles en el interior lo compensaron.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Su salsa verde era muy buena Y picante, la roja era buena pero no demasiado picante.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   El servicio fue excelente y me encanta cmo tienen un fregadero en el rea abierta para lavarse las manos inmediatamente despus de una jugosa birria. No le digas a nadie, pero esto est justo al lado de mi suegras birria.
                  </span>

Upon entering the restaurant, I noticed the beautiful murals featuring famous Mexican mariachi singers - Pedro Infante, Jorge Negrete, Antonio Aguilar...the classics.\n\nAnd this place did not disappoint! We both got the birria de chivo plate which comes with rice, beans and handmade tortillas! Yes, handmade :) Large portions - both my husband and I had some delicious birria leftover. \n\nThere are some bones in the birria, which the tender meat does fall off of (for those that are wary about bones); however there is an abundance of tender and juicy meat. Super flavorful and delicious birria!\n\nI recommend this place, especially if you haven&#x27;t had birria de chivo. Great service, great food, clean restaurant.
